1151→     * Removes one stream thread out of the running stream threads from this Kafka Streams client.
1152→     * <p>
1153→     * The removed stream thread is gracefully shut down. This method does not specify which stream
1154→     * thread is shut down.
1155→     * <p>
1156→     * The consumer associated with the stream thread is closed using consumer.close() during the shutdown process.
1157→     * Note that this method does not guarantee immediate removal of the consumer from the consumer group.
1158→     * The consumer is only kicked off from the group after the stream thread completes its run function.
1159→     * <p>
1160→     * Since the number of stream threads decreases, the sizes of the caches in the remaining stream
1161→     * threads are adapted so that the sum of the cache sizes over all stream threads equals the total
1162→     * cache size specified in configuration {@link StreamsConfig#STATESTORE_CACHE_MAX_BYTES_CONFIG}.
1163→     *
1164→     * @return name of the removed stream thread or empty if a stream thread could not be removed because

1190→    private Optional<String> removeStreamThread(final long timeoutMs) throws TimeoutException {
1191→        final long startMs = time.milliseconds();
1192→
1193→        if (isRunningOrRebalancing()) {
